reviewText: This was a made-for-TV movie. So you can't really expect too much. It was all right. Nothing great, but it works for a decent thriller. It start Judge Reinhold, Timothy Busfield, and Penelope Anne Miller. Basically, there's a killer implanting explosives into pacemakers. Miller is a surgeon with a shady past, Reinhold is the cop trying to stop this and Busfield is the killer. I'd say, if you can find it for a reasonable price go for it, but don't spend too much on it. It's the kind of movie I'd call a lazy Sunday movie. Kill some time, but that's about it.

My sweetheart made me order this for her after seeing part of it on Lifetime, and she watched it and loved it, she wanted me to watch it with her... I guess I understand how she feels about watching sci-fi with me now.

I thought it was okay but, the acting seemed stilted and the story a bit too unbelievable.

Was it the worst thing I've seen this year? No not by a bit...
Would I go tell all my friends to go watch it? No not by a bit.
